  "response": "Yes, anions typically have a larger radius than their corresponding neutral atoms. When an atom gains one or more electrons to become an anion, the added electrons increase electron-electron repulsion within the electron cloud. This repulsion causes the electron cloud to expand, resulting in a larger radius for the anion compared to the neutral atom.",
